WEBVTT

00:01.376 --> 00:03.003
PIPPA:
Why do you call your mom CJ?

00:04.338 --> 00:06.632
- Uh, she lost the privilege
of being called mom.

00:07.132 --> 00:09.259
- Stephen fucking DeMarco.

00:09.259 --> 00:10.886
STEPHEN:
Macy, how are you?

00:10.886 --> 00:12.137
- You guys know each other?

00:12.137 --> 00:13.597
- We're both from Bayville.

00:13.597 --> 00:15.265
- Who was calling you yesterday?
LUCY: My mom.

00:15.265 --> 00:17.142
She did something really fucked up,

00:17.142 --> 00:20.729
and... I, I can't really
forgive her for it.

00:20.729 --> 00:21.980
I've tried.

00:21.980 --> 00:23.148
- My mom's difficult, too.

00:23.148 --> 00:24.358
I don't even talk to my dad.

00:25.067 --> 00:26.777
He left when I was six.

00:27.694 --> 00:28.862
This one won't die.

00:33.492 --> 00:35.118
LUCY:
Just shit with Stephen.

00:35.118 --> 00:38.038
Like, I'm being so stupid,
I don't even feel like myself.

00:38.038 --> 00:39.540
- There are other people out there.

00:39.540 --> 00:41.583
What about that guy that we met?

00:41.583 --> 00:42.668
- Max.

00:43.752 --> 00:46.463
You still wanna grab dinner sometime?

00:46.463 --> 00:47.881
[laughs]

00:47.881 --> 00:50.843
♪

00:50.843 --> 00:53.011
♪

00:59.059 --> 01:03.397
♪

01:10.195 --> 01:12.656
[coffee pouring]

01:12.656 --> 01:14.491
[Max sighs]

01:14.491 --> 01:16.159
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

01:16.159 --> 01:17.870
MAX:
Only the best coffee for you.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.331
- My favorite.

01:22.416 --> 01:23.959
Hmm. Yum.

01:23.959 --> 01:25.878
[phone buzzing]

01:31.175 --> 01:32.176
Oh shit.

01:33.177 --> 01:36.263
- What?
- I, uh, I gotta go pack.

01:36.263 --> 01:37.472
My mom's about to be here.

01:38.640 --> 01:40.559
- Let me know if you need rescuing.

01:40.559 --> 01:41.643
- Thank you.

01:42.477 --> 01:43.937
And if I don't talk to you?

01:44.396 --> 01:45.898
- Because phones don't exist?

01:46.398 --> 01:48.108
[both chuckle]

01:48.525 --> 01:50.485
- Merry Christmas, just in case.

01:50.903 --> 01:52.237
- Alright.

01:52.237 --> 01:53.614
Merry Christmas, weirdo.

01:53.614 --> 01:56.074
♪ Are you the brutal heart ♪

01:57.826 --> 02:02.414
♪ Are you the brutal heart
that I've been looking for ♪

02:02.915 --> 02:05.167
♪ 'Cause if you're looking for love ♪

02:05.167 --> 02:07.669
♪ You can look for that door ♪

02:08.587 --> 02:09.755
LUCY:
Hi.

02:09.755 --> 02:11.340
- Didn't realize you weren't home.

02:11.340 --> 02:13.008
- Weren't you leaving last night?

02:13.884 --> 02:15.636
- Delaying the inevitable.

02:16.094 --> 02:17.679
- Hi.
- Hi.

02:22.100 --> 02:23.101
- Come in.

02:25.729 --> 02:28.815
♪ So use ♪

02:29.149 --> 02:30.609
STEPHEN:
Late night?

02:31.693 --> 02:34.655
- Yeah, some of the girls
and I got pretty hammered.

02:34.947 --> 02:38.075
Just mentally preparing to be
with my mom for two weeks.

02:38.534 --> 02:39.535
Come here.

02:40.869 --> 02:43.121
♪ I don't mind at all ♪

02:44.790 --> 02:46.750
- Did you smell me?
- Mm-hmm.

02:48.043 --> 02:51.255
You just smell so much like you.

02:54.049 --> 02:56.301
Like more than you
normally smell like you.

02:56.301 --> 02:57.678
- Probably my sweatshirt.

02:57.678 --> 02:58.679
♪ Hearts ♪

03:00.389 --> 03:03.809
♪ And hearts that break
the night in two ♪

03:04.768 --> 03:05.769
[phone rings]

03:05.769 --> 03:07.813
♪ And arms that can't hold ♪

03:07.813 --> 03:09.481
LUCY:
Oh my god, sorry.

03:09.481 --> 03:10.899
STEPHEN:
Just take it.

03:11.483 --> 03:12.860
- Hi, what is it?

03:12.860 --> 03:15.404
CJ:
Hi, I just pulled onto campus.

03:16.029 --> 03:18.448
- Okay, I'll, I'll be down in a minute.

03:18.448 --> 03:19.533
- CJ:
Okay, bye.

03:19.950 --> 03:21.827
♪ Bitter hearts ♪

03:21.827 --> 03:25.330
- I'm sorry, she wasn't supposed
to be here for another hour.

03:25.330 --> 03:28.083
Maybe we can finish this over break?

03:28.083 --> 03:29.835
It's gonna be weird not seeing you

03:29.835 --> 03:32.045
when we're only like
a half hour from each other.

03:32.045 --> 03:33.380
- Yeah, for sure.

03:33.380 --> 03:34.798
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

03:34.798 --> 03:36.592
- Cool, what, what day do you think?

03:37.843 --> 03:41.513
- Uh... what's good for you,
what works?

03:42.639 --> 03:47.102
- Day after Christmas is a pretty great
black hole of a day.

03:47.102 --> 03:48.353
- Okay.
- Okay.

03:51.273 --> 03:52.441
Alright, I gotta go.

03:55.277 --> 03:56.278
Okay.

03:57.821 --> 03:59.156
- Bye.
- Bye.

03:59.156 --> 04:02.284
♪ This night from black to blue ♪

04:02.284 --> 04:03.452
[door opens]

04:05.871 --> 04:06.872
[door closes]

04:06.872 --> 04:11.376
♪ So use me ♪

04:13.879 --> 04:18.926
♪ Use me ♪

04:18.926 --> 04:23.597
[brakes hiss, bus rumbling]
[people chattering]

04:26.016 --> 04:27.142
- Hey.
STEPHEN: Hey.

04:29.603 --> 04:31.772
Are you allowed to drive on your own?

04:32.105 --> 04:33.649
- With a licensed driver in the car.

04:34.566 --> 04:36.818
- Oh, so you only broke
the law on the way here.

04:37.486 --> 04:38.487
- Exactly.

04:39.821 --> 04:41.698
[engine rumbling]

04:42.282 --> 04:46.203
- So... how are spirits?

04:46.620 --> 04:50.541
- Well, she loves the holidays, so

04:52.835 --> 04:54.211
weirdly kinda high.

04:54.837 --> 04:55.838
- Yeah.

05:01.218 --> 05:03.762
[dog barking]

05:04.346 --> 05:07.558
[doors creaking]

05:09.768 --> 05:11.562
SADIE: Hey.
- [hushed voice] She's got a migraine.

05:11.562 --> 05:14.106
She's lying down in her room,
so I told her we'd keep everything quiet.

05:23.323 --> 05:24.366
Good to see you.

05:25.409 --> 05:26.410
- [hushed voice] You too.

05:30.706 --> 05:31.707
- How was the trip?

05:32.291 --> 05:33.333
- Fine, you know.

05:33.709 --> 05:35.335
- [hushed voice]
How long has she been out for?

05:35.335 --> 05:36.336
- Like an hour.

05:37.546 --> 05:39.673
- Are you sure we shouldn't go say hi?

05:39.673 --> 05:42.009
- She specifically said
not to wake her up.

05:42.009 --> 05:43.010
- Okay.

05:44.803 --> 05:46.471
Is there anything to eat, food?

05:46.471 --> 05:47.681
- There's some frozen--

05:47.681 --> 05:49.725
- Just wait, the microwave is so loud.

05:49.725 --> 05:50.976
NORA:
Is that Stephen?

05:50.976 --> 05:52.436
Is he home?

05:53.061 --> 05:54.563
- Yeah, Mom.

05:54.563 --> 05:55.647
Sorry about the noise.

06:04.406 --> 06:06.366
[floorboards creak]

06:17.085 --> 06:18.086
- Hey, Mom.

06:20.547 --> 06:22.466
- Oh...
- Happy holidays.

06:25.469 --> 06:27.429
- Why didn't you come say hi to me?

06:28.472 --> 06:29.932
STEPHEN:
I'm sorry, I should have.

06:30.557 --> 06:33.268
Vince said you have a migraine.

06:35.145 --> 06:36.146
- It's okay.

06:36.813 --> 06:37.814
Come here.

06:42.736 --> 06:43.862
Hi.
- Hi.

06:45.239 --> 06:47.032
[pats back]

06:51.453 --> 06:53.247
- Just come say hi to me next time.

06:54.164 --> 06:58.836
♪

06:58.836 --> 06:59.837
- Sorry.

07:01.338 --> 07:04.299
♪

07:04.299 --> 07:07.302
♪

07:07.302 --> 07:08.303
- You're forgiven.

07:09.346 --> 07:14.351
♪

07:18.522 --> 07:20.232
GEORGIA: Morning.
- Hey.

07:20.232 --> 07:21.358
CJ:
Hey, you're up.

07:22.067 --> 07:23.735
- Yeah.
- CJ: Um, something came for you.

07:24.361 --> 07:25.362
- Ooh.

07:33.328 --> 07:36.373
It's a memorial for Macy,

07:36.373 --> 07:38.667
on the 27th,
at her house in Bayville.

07:39.334 --> 07:41.003
- Oh, I'm sorry.

07:41.420 --> 07:42.421
You should go.

07:45.007 --> 07:46.550
[phone buzzes]

07:49.052 --> 07:50.971
- Oh my god!
- What?

07:50.971 --> 07:53.015
- I, I got into
the advanced writing seminar.

07:53.015 --> 07:55.142
- I knew you would.
- Wait, what seminar?

07:55.142 --> 07:56.810
- It's, it's a next semester thing.

07:56.810 --> 07:58.604
They don't even accept
a lot of freshmen.

07:58.604 --> 07:59.813
- That's so great!

08:01.815 --> 08:04.943
Hey, um, so, do you think
that I'll get to meet

08:04.943 --> 08:06.528
this guy that you're seeing?

08:06.528 --> 08:07.905
- What?
- The one from Bayville?

08:07.905 --> 08:09.031
- Georgia.
- Mom!

08:09.990 --> 08:12.117
I just said that you were
kinda hanging out with someone,

08:12.117 --> 08:14.369
and I specifically told her
that she was not allowed

08:14.369 --> 08:16.079
to clarify what hanging out meant.

08:16.079 --> 08:17.080
[CJ chuckles]

08:17.664 --> 08:18.665
- There you go.

08:19.499 --> 08:20.709
Oh, just give me something.

08:21.543 --> 08:24.588
- What, I don't know.
He goes to my school.

08:24.588 --> 08:26.840
CJ: Mm-hmm.
- Wants to be a lawyer.

08:26.840 --> 08:28.175
- Lawyer, I like that.

08:28.175 --> 08:29.551
- I'm sure you do.

08:29.551 --> 08:30.886
[CJ laughs]

08:31.512 --> 08:32.804
- I'm so happy you're home.

08:33.514 --> 08:34.556
[doorbell rings]
[dog barks]

08:34.556 --> 08:35.557
- I'll get that.

08:37.476 --> 08:39.019
Gus, shh.

08:42.064 --> 08:43.565
- Hey, Lucy.

08:43.565 --> 08:44.566
It's been a while.

08:44.566 --> 08:45.901
Merry Christmas.

08:46.568 --> 08:48.362
- Merry Christmas, James.

08:48.362 --> 08:49.696
- How're you liking Baird?

08:49.696 --> 08:51.698
- It's, yeah, it's good. It's fine.

08:52.407 --> 08:54.326
- Oh, James, hi.
What are you doing here?

08:54.326 --> 08:55.869
- I'm sorry, I should've called first.

08:55.869 --> 08:57.079
- No, don't be silly, come in.

08:57.079 --> 08:58.830
Are you gonna let him freeze
on the front doorstep?

08:58.830 --> 09:00.374
JAMES: It's fine.
GEORGIA: I'll have those.

09:00.374 --> 09:02.417
CJ: How've you been?
JAMES: Just came to drop that off.

09:02.417 --> 09:03.752
CJ:
That was very sweet of you.

09:04.294 --> 09:08.715
♪

09:10.801 --> 09:12.678
Hey.
- Hi.

09:12.678 --> 09:13.929
- What on earth was that?

09:14.638 --> 09:15.889
LUCY:
What was what?

09:15.889 --> 09:18.642
- You, you were acting very cold.

09:22.604 --> 09:24.022
- Does he come by here a lot?

09:24.606 --> 09:28.569
- Well, I don't know what you consider
a lot, um, but why?

09:30.070 --> 09:31.071
Lucy.

09:32.489 --> 09:34.032
- Why did you put up Dad's stocking?

09:35.784 --> 09:37.578
- Because your grandparents
came by this week

09:37.578 --> 09:38.829
to drop off the presents.

09:38.829 --> 09:40.414
- So you put it up for them?

09:40.414 --> 09:42.708
- I thought that that would be nice
for them. They're his parents.

09:42.708 --> 09:44.877
- We haven't put it up in three years.

09:44.877 --> 09:47.004
- It's a stocking.
What's the issue?

09:47.004 --> 09:49.047
- I just don't understand
putting it up for appearances.

09:49.047 --> 09:51.550
What are you worried about,
that they don't think you're sad enough?

09:52.593 --> 09:54.636
- [sighs] Wow.

10:04.438 --> 10:05.439
STEPHEN:
Where'd you find it?

10:06.315 --> 10:07.566
- Him.

10:07.566 --> 10:09.276
He was out by the garage.

10:09.276 --> 10:11.486
I checked with the neighbors,
but he's not any of theirs.

10:11.486 --> 10:14.364
- He smells, and his litter smells.

10:15.199 --> 10:16.783
- I'm not keeping him for long,

10:16.783 --> 10:18.577
just until we can find him a home.

10:19.161 --> 10:21.288
- Yeah, well, he'd probably find
a home on his own

10:21.288 --> 10:23.165
if you'd stop feeding him so much.

10:23.790 --> 10:25.209
Cats are smart like that.

10:25.667 --> 10:27.085
- You look really pretty today, Mom.

10:31.673 --> 10:33.175
- You do.
- Mm-hmm.

10:33.842 --> 10:36.512
Says the boy who doesn't come
say hi to me.

10:39.139 --> 10:42.226
So, did Vince tell you his big news?

10:44.645 --> 10:46.271
- I'm moving back to Bayville.

10:46.271 --> 10:47.856
- What? What about your job?

10:47.856 --> 10:49.149
- That's a silly question.

10:49.149 --> 10:51.151
He can be an accountant anywhere.

10:51.151 --> 10:53.445
- I got offered a job
at a firm in Long Beach.

10:53.445 --> 10:55.989
- Oh, so you just decided
you didn't like the city anymore?

10:55.989 --> 10:57.658
- I do, but Mom's here.

11:01.870 --> 11:03.247
- How does the pay compare to the city?

11:03.247 --> 11:05.832
- Okay, Stephen, grocery store.

11:08.126 --> 11:09.169
Let's go.

11:09.169 --> 11:12.714
[people chattering]

11:17.386 --> 11:18.762
Thanks for helping out, Stephen.

11:20.514 --> 11:21.932
You know, I was thinking,

11:21.932 --> 11:25.727
what if I took us all out for
a fancy meal on Christmas Eve?

11:26.478 --> 11:27.896
We never go out.

11:27.896 --> 11:28.897
- We can't afford it.

11:29.731 --> 11:31.275
- Oh, it's a holiday.

11:32.359 --> 11:35.320
I was thinking of maybe,
maybe Basil Leaf.

11:36.613 --> 11:37.906
- Basil Leaf is good.

11:38.657 --> 11:40.117
- What about Louie's?

11:40.868 --> 11:43.370
Everyone says that's the best.

11:43.954 --> 11:45.622
- I've heard that, yeah, Louie's.

11:47.207 --> 11:50.169
- So, Louie's is what you'd prefer?

11:51.712 --> 11:52.713
- Sure, yeah.

11:53.422 --> 11:54.423
Louie's.

11:56.175 --> 11:57.342
- Great.

11:57.342 --> 12:00.262
Let's, uh, stop at the flower shop
on the way home,

12:00.262 --> 12:02.306
the one in Glen Head.

12:02.306 --> 12:03.307
STEPHEN:
There's a closer one.

12:04.016 --> 12:05.350
- Yeah, that one's shit.

12:06.643 --> 12:07.686
Take the cart back.

12:11.690 --> 12:12.858
[bell tinkles]

12:13.483 --> 12:16.653
[people murmuring]

12:21.533 --> 12:22.576
- What kind do you want?

12:23.952 --> 12:25.871
- Uh, well...

12:27.706 --> 12:29.082
what are holiday colors?

12:31.502 --> 12:34.463
- Red, green, red and green?

12:36.423 --> 12:37.424
- Okay.

12:38.300 --> 12:39.968
I'll get some red roses.
- Okay.

12:45.432 --> 12:48.644
[people murmuring]

12:55.108 --> 12:57.277
- Merry Christmas.
WOMAN: You too.

12:57.277 --> 13:00.280
♪

13:00.280 --> 13:02.991
♪

13:02.991 --> 13:04.910
♪

13:04.910 --> 13:06.411
- Do you come in here a lot?

13:07.329 --> 13:08.997
- Here?
- Mm-hmm.

13:08.997 --> 13:10.582
- Yeah, I've been here a few times.

13:15.838 --> 13:17.297
STEPHEN: Does that woman
know you or something?

13:19.633 --> 13:20.843
- These are nice.

13:20.843 --> 13:22.219
- Yeah.

13:22.719 --> 13:23.929
They're not roses.

13:25.222 --> 13:26.765
- Take 'em up to the counter for me.

13:31.061 --> 13:33.480
- You want these? Okay.
- Mm-hmm.

13:33.480 --> 13:37.276
♪

13:37.276 --> 13:39.570
♪

13:39.570 --> 13:42.656
♪

13:42.656 --> 13:43.866
STEPHEN:
How have you been doing lately?

13:44.908 --> 13:47.035
- Me? I'm good.
- Mm-hmm.

13:47.744 --> 13:49.371
- I'm happy your brother's moving home.

13:50.330 --> 13:51.874
It's nice how much he cares.

13:53.375 --> 13:54.668
- Who was the woman?

13:55.586 --> 13:56.962
- Which woman?

13:56.962 --> 13:59.131
- The flower shop,
behind the counter.

13:59.131 --> 14:03.802
- Oh, she was
a flower shop employee.

14:05.679 --> 14:06.680
- Do you know her?

14:07.598 --> 14:09.266
She looked like
she recognized you or something.

14:09.266 --> 14:10.809
- Did she?
- Mm-hmm.

14:14.563 --> 14:15.689
- She was pretty.

14:18.025 --> 14:19.484
- I didn't really look at her.

14:20.485 --> 14:23.322
- You looked at her enough
to observe her behavior.

14:23.322 --> 14:25.157
Certainly, you looked at her long enough

14:25.157 --> 14:26.909
to know if you thought she was pretty.

14:27.784 --> 14:29.119
- Did, did you think she was pretty?

14:29.870 --> 14:31.163
- I'm asking if you did.

14:33.040 --> 14:34.958
- No, no, I didn't, not really.

14:34.958 --> 14:35.959
[Nora scoffs]

14:36.543 --> 14:39.421
- I don't know how you could think
that she wasn't pretty.

14:41.173 --> 14:43.175
- Mom, if there's something
going on with that woman

14:43.175 --> 14:44.635
or anything, you can tell me.

14:46.011 --> 14:47.513
I just want to make sure
everything's okay.

14:47.513 --> 14:49.723
- Of course, everything's okay.

14:49.723 --> 14:51.350
- Alright, I'm just checking.
- I mean,

14:51.350 --> 14:54.269
why won't you just admit
that she's pretty?

14:54.853 --> 14:56.855
I can handle
another woman being pretty.

14:56.855 --> 14:58.482
I'm not that insecure.

14:58.482 --> 15:00.943
- No. Mom, I'm not saying
you're insecure.

15:00.943 --> 15:02.903
I didn't think you were insecure.
That's not what I was saying.

15:02.903 --> 15:04.738
- If a woman is objectively pretty,

15:04.738 --> 15:05.864
why don't you just say it?

15:05.864 --> 15:07.199
- I didn't think she was pretty, Mom.

15:07.199 --> 15:08.951
That's, that's what I'm saying.
- Stephen!

15:08.951 --> 15:10.827
- Okay, okay.
- Why-- Please stop doing this.

15:10.827 --> 15:12.246
- Okay, she's pretty.

15:12.246 --> 15:13.872
She was pretty. Okay?

15:14.623 --> 15:16.124
[Nora sighs]
- Alright?

15:17.543 --> 15:21.755
♪

15:23.257 --> 15:26.593
[phone beeping]

15:26.593 --> 15:27.761
[phone buzzes]

15:29.012 --> 15:31.306
[dog barking]

15:31.306 --> 15:34.518
♪

15:34.518 --> 15:37.062
♪

15:37.062 --> 15:38.063
[phone beeps]

15:39.857 --> 15:42.067
[line rings]

15:42.067 --> 15:44.152
[phone buzzing]
[door opens]

15:44.570 --> 15:45.779
SADIE:
Stephen?

15:46.947 --> 15:47.948
Hey.

15:48.490 --> 15:50.742
Mom went on a walk with Vince.

15:50.742 --> 15:52.244
You don't have to hide out here.

15:52.244 --> 15:54.496
- I'm not hiding.
I'm avoiding.

15:59.835 --> 16:01.420
- I fucking hate it here.

16:04.423 --> 16:05.716
- You'll be in college soon enough.

16:06.633 --> 16:07.634
- Two years.

16:08.260 --> 16:11.054
- Hm?
If I did it, you can do it.

16:13.307 --> 16:14.725
- For my birthday last month,

16:14.725 --> 16:17.186
I asked her if I could have a party
with some of my friends

16:17.186 --> 16:18.770
instead of staying home with her,

16:18.770 --> 16:21.523
she barely spoke to me
for, like, a week.

16:22.316 --> 16:23.942
- Yeah, should've seen that coming.

16:25.652 --> 16:27.738
- I just thought maybe
she'd get better one day.

16:28.947 --> 16:31.241
- Yeah, people like her don't get better.

16:32.075 --> 16:33.785
She is who she is.

16:35.829 --> 16:38.123
- I've been looking at brochures
for boarding schools.

16:39.124 --> 16:40.959
- Why, to remind yourself
that you're poor?

16:40.959 --> 16:43.128
- A lot of them have financial aid.

16:43.837 --> 16:47.299
There's one in Jersey
I'm pretty sure I could get into.

16:48.884 --> 16:50.636
My guidance counselor says I could.

16:56.266 --> 16:57.267
[Sadie chuckles]

16:59.353 --> 17:01.271
- It's gonna get really ugly,
you know that, right?

17:04.983 --> 17:06.860
- I can't be here anymore, Stephen.

17:12.616 --> 17:15.619
[sighs]

17:18.705 --> 17:20.207
- You can't tell her you talked
to me about it.

17:22.334 --> 17:25.546
She'll feel like we were...

17:25.546 --> 17:27.631
plotting against her,
and then she'll freak.

17:28.507 --> 17:33.136
But... if you think you can get in,

17:34.012 --> 17:35.013
apply.

17:39.893 --> 17:41.228
She'll never forgive you, though.

17:43.605 --> 17:46.900
- I need a parent's signature
for the application.

17:54.199 --> 17:55.200
- Fill 'em out.

17:59.121 --> 18:00.122
Give 'em to me.

18:01.164 --> 18:02.291
I'll figure something out.

18:09.756 --> 18:12.593
[camera shutter clicks]
[people chattering]

18:13.260 --> 18:14.261
[Lucy sighs]

18:17.806 --> 18:18.891
LYDIA:
Just for you.

18:19.933 --> 18:22.019
- I forgot how perfect your joints are.

18:22.019 --> 18:23.020
[chuckles]

18:23.020 --> 18:25.022
So dainty and ladylike.

18:25.022 --> 18:27.357
- Nobody at school appreciates them.

18:27.357 --> 18:29.276
- Fucking ungrateful monsters.

18:29.276 --> 18:30.861
[Lydia laughs]
I'll kill 'em.

18:32.654 --> 18:34.656
- I miss you so much.
- I miss you.

18:38.577 --> 18:41.747
Do your parents ever see
my mom out, like, socially?

18:41.747 --> 18:42.956
- Why?

18:42.956 --> 18:45.334
- I'm just wondering who
she's been spending time with.

18:46.168 --> 18:47.669
- Hey, Lucy.

18:48.378 --> 18:49.755
LUCY:
Hey, Rob.

18:49.755 --> 18:51.924
- Hey, can I take some of the whiskey
from your dad's bar?

18:52.466 --> 18:54.009
- Just not the expensive stuff.

18:54.009 --> 18:55.552
- Sweet. Hey, Lucy.

18:56.845 --> 18:59.473
You look good.
Looks like you avoided freshman 15.

19:01.683 --> 19:03.644
- I'm sorry.
- Wow.

19:03.644 --> 19:05.270
- He overcompensates because
he thinks that you hate him.

19:05.270 --> 19:07.189
- I don't hate him.
Your mom hates him.

19:08.398 --> 19:11.360
Can't believe you guys stayed together
a whole semester. Crazy.

19:12.069 --> 19:13.820
- We visited each other a lot.

19:14.905 --> 19:15.906
LUCY:
Yeah.

19:17.115 --> 19:19.326
- I hate that he goes
to the same school as Laura,

19:19.326 --> 19:21.495
but he swears that nothing's
happened between them, so.

19:22.079 --> 19:23.830
I wish that you'd invited Stephen.

19:23.830 --> 19:25.958
- We're not really at that place yet.

19:25.958 --> 19:28.043
We're keeping it casual, and it's fine.

19:28.043 --> 19:30.128
- You told me about him,
like, week two of school.

19:30.128 --> 19:31.213
What are you talking about?

19:37.010 --> 19:38.303
[Nora exhales]

19:42.015 --> 19:43.016
- You look fancy.

19:44.601 --> 19:46.019
- Don't sound so surprised.

19:50.858 --> 19:51.984
Okay, guys, let's go.

19:52.693 --> 19:55.654
[people chattering]

20:03.161 --> 20:04.454
- Here you go,
server will be right with you.

20:04.454 --> 20:05.455
- Thank you.

20:07.916 --> 20:08.917
HOST:
Merry Christmas.

20:11.336 --> 20:12.337
- Thank you.

20:17.634 --> 20:18.635
Very nice.

20:20.345 --> 20:22.514
I thought we might, uh, start

20:22.514 --> 20:25.392
with a nice bottle of white for the table.

20:25.392 --> 20:27.561
What do you think, Vince?
- Yeah, sounds good.

20:28.061 --> 20:29.855
Should we let Stephen use his fake?

20:29.855 --> 20:31.440
[Nora laughs]

20:31.440 --> 20:33.650
- I'm not supposed to know
anything about that.

20:35.027 --> 20:37.946
♪ light jazz music playing ♪

20:48.582 --> 20:49.791
- Mom?

20:49.791 --> 20:51.543
- Oh god, why is Dad here?

20:52.461 --> 20:53.462
- What are you doing?

20:55.672 --> 20:57.966
Why is he here?
- How would I know?

20:58.717 --> 20:59.801
It's a coincidence.

21:00.552 --> 21:02.137
- Jesus Christ.

21:02.137 --> 21:03.597
- Merry Christmas.

21:03.597 --> 21:05.015
May I take your drink orders?

21:05.015 --> 21:07.351
NORA: Uh, yes, we'd like--
- Should we leave?

21:07.351 --> 21:10.229
- Uh, we would like a bottle
of Sauvignon Blanc,

21:10.229 --> 21:11.939
whichever you recommend,

21:11.939 --> 21:13.524
and waters for the table.

21:16.193 --> 21:18.028
- You told me
you didn't know that woman.

21:18.028 --> 21:19.029
- Who is she?

21:20.572 --> 21:21.573
The woman.

21:22.115 --> 21:23.909
- I think we should just leave.

21:23.909 --> 21:25.994
- Yeah.
- Why don't we just go home?

21:25.994 --> 21:28.497
- No, we are not going anywhere.

21:30.040 --> 21:32.835
- You've gotta stop this.
The fuck is wrong with you?

21:32.835 --> 21:33.961
- Excuse me?

21:34.753 --> 21:37.589
I'm here having a nice lunch
with my children.

21:37.589 --> 21:39.383
You're the one making a scene.

21:41.802 --> 21:45.264
Uh, just go ahead and pour
the glass, thank you.

21:45.264 --> 21:47.307
- Abby told me you came to her work.

21:49.685 --> 21:52.896
- Uh, we'll, we'll order our food
in just a minute, thank you.

21:54.439 --> 21:55.607
- I feel sorry for you.

21:56.525 --> 21:57.860
And for you three.

21:58.861 --> 22:00.320
That you have to watch her do this.

22:00.320 --> 22:03.407
♪

22:08.412 --> 22:13.125
♪

22:17.337 --> 22:19.464
- Oh my god!

22:24.553 --> 22:26.221
Why do you do this?

22:27.556 --> 22:28.974
- Do what?

22:28.974 --> 22:30.309
This isn't my fault.

22:30.309 --> 22:31.768
- That woman was pregnant.

22:35.189 --> 22:37.399
NORA:
Well, maybe it's better that you know.

22:38.400 --> 22:40.569
♪

22:43.071 --> 22:46.200
[cat meowing]

22:47.159 --> 22:51.413
- So, I guess I just let
you all down, I get it.

22:52.456 --> 22:54.750
Buy you lunch I can barely afford,

22:54.750 --> 22:57.127
but I am a terrible, worthless mother.

22:58.253 --> 22:59.630
- No one thinks that, Mom.

22:59.630 --> 23:01.673
- Yeah, then why are you
treating me that way?

23:02.508 --> 23:04.927
I try to do something nice for you
and you're punishing me.

23:04.927 --> 23:07.221
VINCE: No one is punishing you.
I think we're just a little upset.

23:07.221 --> 23:08.597
- Yeah, what about me?

23:09.890 --> 23:11.308
What about me?

23:11.308 --> 23:12.351
How do you think I feel?

23:12.893 --> 23:14.311
I didn't plan today.

23:14.978 --> 23:16.021
And besides...

23:16.688 --> 23:19.066
who cares if we ruined his lunch?

23:19.816 --> 23:21.527
Shouldn't he have to be accountable?

23:22.778 --> 23:24.696
He should have to see what he's missing.

23:29.409 --> 23:31.411
- So you just didn't know
he was gonna be there?

23:31.411 --> 23:33.789
- [scoffs] No.

23:34.873 --> 23:37.167
[sniffles]
No, honey. I...

23:38.460 --> 23:40.379
I had no idea.

23:41.797 --> 23:42.798
Besides,

23:44.758 --> 23:47.052
I wasn't even the one
who chose that restaurant.

23:49.012 --> 23:50.097
Stephen did.

23:55.018 --> 23:56.061
- This is bullshit.

24:06.321 --> 24:07.322
[sighs]

24:12.160 --> 24:14.037
- You know you chose that restaurant.

24:17.624 --> 24:18.625
[chuckles]

24:18.625 --> 24:22.087
♪

24:22.087 --> 24:25.757
♪

24:25.757 --> 24:27.885
LUCY:
Ooh, that's nice.

24:27.885 --> 24:28.886
GEORGIA:
Is it new?

24:31.221 --> 24:33.807
- Wow, who gave you that?
- Huh?

24:34.141 --> 24:36.602
- Who gave you the necklace?
- Oh, um, uh, my...

24:37.477 --> 24:38.729
my friend.

24:38.729 --> 24:41.440
♪ One night to be confused ♪

24:41.440 --> 24:43.817
♪ One night to speed up truth ♪

24:44.193 --> 24:46.653
♪ We had a promise made ♪

24:48.113 --> 24:49.239
[line ringing]

24:50.240 --> 24:52.492
[phone buzzes]

24:53.160 --> 24:55.287
- Hey, merry Christmas.

24:55.287 --> 24:58.040
- Hi. Merry Christmas.

24:58.040 --> 25:00.083
- Wanna know what I'm wearing?
- Okay.

25:00.083 --> 25:01.543
Yeah, what are you wearing?

25:01.543 --> 25:03.212
- Your sweatshirt.

25:03.629 --> 25:04.963
You left it in my room.

25:04.963 --> 25:07.633
- I really like that visual.
I hope you're naked underneath it.

25:07.633 --> 25:10.093
- [chuckles]
How's your Christmas?

25:10.093 --> 25:12.346
STEPHEN:
Um, it's not the best.

25:12.346 --> 25:15.682
My family's... you know, uh,

25:16.266 --> 25:17.309
they're hard.

25:17.309 --> 25:18.769
LUCY:
Oh my god, you have no idea.

25:18.769 --> 25:20.979
Everyone here is so dysfunctional.

25:21.438 --> 25:25.275
- Oh, I'd probably get it
more than you think.

25:25.275 --> 25:27.861
- There is no way your mom
is as bad as mine.

25:28.570 --> 25:29.571
- Yeah.

25:32.991 --> 25:33.992
Probably not.

25:34.451 --> 25:35.452
Um...

25:37.037 --> 25:38.330
well, I just wanted to say hi.

25:39.498 --> 25:40.666
- Oh, okay.

25:40.666 --> 25:43.335
Um... are we still on for tomorrow?

25:43.335 --> 25:48.549
- Shit, um, I don't think
I can do that anymore.

25:49.883 --> 25:54.054
- Really? I, I just, just...
scheduled things around that.

25:54.054 --> 25:58.225
- It's just, this family stuff
is really stressing me out.

25:58.225 --> 26:00.727
- Well, maybe I can be your distraction.

26:00.727 --> 26:01.812
- Yeah, we can

26:03.647 --> 26:04.690
talk tomorrow

26:05.899 --> 26:06.900
and figure it out.

26:06.900 --> 26:09.486
Um, I should go open presents.

26:09.945 --> 26:11.530
Okay, I'll, I'll call you later.

26:11.530 --> 26:12.698
- Okay, bye.

26:13.824 --> 26:15.534
♪ To lean on ♪

26:15.534 --> 26:20.205
♪ Wouldn't be good enough ♪

26:20.205 --> 26:22.708
♪ And you ♪

26:23.458 --> 26:26.795
♪ You knew the hand of the devil ♪

26:28.422 --> 26:30.507
[line ringing]

26:32.342 --> 26:33.886
- Hi, Max.

26:35.888 --> 26:36.889
- Thank you, Mom.

26:39.600 --> 26:40.851
Sadie, you wanna open one?

26:40.851 --> 26:44.104
♪ In one night ♪

26:47.316 --> 26:50.694
♪ To call for hands of above ♪

26:50.694 --> 26:52.196
- Hey.
- Hi.

26:52.196 --> 26:54.323
CJ: What's the bag for?
- I'm gonna go to Lydia's.

26:54.323 --> 26:55.324
- What?

26:55.949 --> 26:58.243
It's Christmas, I rented "The Holiday."

26:58.619 --> 27:02.664
- Yeah, but the day's over and, you know,
she's having guy troubles, so--

27:03.749 --> 27:06.126
- You know what, just go to Lydia's.

27:08.587 --> 27:09.588
- Okay.

27:11.089 --> 27:13.759
DIANA: [on phone] Look,
your mom's always gonna be your mom.

27:14.593 --> 27:17.596
Did you send in those
internship applications I found?

27:17.596 --> 27:18.972
My dad says they're legit.

27:18.972 --> 27:20.724
- I sent them before I left campus.

27:21.266 --> 27:22.851
DIANA:
Good. See?

27:23.393 --> 27:24.478
Things will get better.

27:26.522 --> 27:28.065
You're not okay.

27:28.065 --> 27:29.691
Why don't I come out to Bayville?

27:29.691 --> 27:31.360
- You don't want to be in this house.

27:32.194 --> 27:33.570
DIANA:
But you want me to come.

27:37.157 --> 27:38.158
- I should go

27:38.909 --> 27:40.619
before my mom comes looking for me.

27:41.787 --> 27:43.789
DIANA: If you don't want me
to come, then tell me now.

27:48.210 --> 27:52.339
- Uh, okay, I'm gonna call you later.

27:53.006 --> 27:54.967
DIANA:
Okay. Bye.

27:55.926 --> 27:57.970
[crickets chirping]

27:58.804 --> 28:01.014
[footsteps approaching]

28:02.057 --> 28:03.058
- Hello.

28:10.190 --> 28:12.484
- I can't believe you
booty called me on Christmas.

28:12.484 --> 28:14.695
- [Lucy laughs]
Come on.

28:18.115 --> 28:20.534
Thank you.
Oh, can we have extra syrup, too?

28:20.993 --> 28:22.578
A-and whipped cream?

28:23.453 --> 28:24.997
Okay, thank you.

28:25.747 --> 28:28.375
[water trickling]

28:32.838 --> 28:37.342
So, I think I ordered food for six of us.

28:38.427 --> 28:39.428
- Just six?

28:57.196 --> 29:01.575
♪

29:18.926 --> 29:21.136
- ANNOUNCER: [on TV]
They've bounced back after a bad season

29:21.136 --> 29:23.347
for a game record,

29:23.347 --> 29:25.849
and right now they're
already seeking season two

29:25.849 --> 29:27.434
and looking to hold it.

29:27.434 --> 29:28.727
Yeah, nobody saw that coming,

29:28.727 --> 29:30.562
and after last season,
they've both got to--

29:30.562 --> 29:31.688
[knocking on door]

29:37.236 --> 29:38.570
- Surprise!

29:39.154 --> 29:40.531
- Hi.
- Hi.

29:44.034 --> 29:46.078
You didn't tell me not to come.

29:47.120 --> 29:48.121
- I feel bad.

29:48.121 --> 29:50.499
If I had known
you actually liked your family,

29:50.499 --> 29:52.751
I wouldn't have made you
ditch them on Christmas.

29:52.751 --> 29:54.253
- I guess it's my fault.

29:56.338 --> 29:57.673
I always come when you call.

29:59.675 --> 30:01.301
- Well, thank you for coming.

30:01.301 --> 30:03.846
I really needed an escape from my mom.

30:03.846 --> 30:05.639
- It sounds like she's just lonely.

30:10.519 --> 30:13.355
What is it about her
that bugs you so much?

30:13.355 --> 30:14.565
- It's not a very good story.

30:19.653 --> 30:20.779
- I don't need it to be.

30:27.703 --> 30:28.704
- Um...

30:31.623 --> 30:34.001
my dad died when I was 15.

30:36.670 --> 30:37.671
- Ah, man.

30:39.173 --> 30:40.174
I'm so sorry.

30:41.049 --> 30:42.759
- Thanks. He was...

30:44.511 --> 30:46.847
he was sick for a really long time, and...

30:48.849 --> 30:50.809
at one point, we thought
he was gonna get better,

30:50.809 --> 30:55.147
but then... it became clear
that he wasn't.

30:57.399 --> 30:59.902
So we took him home
for the last couple months and

31:01.695 --> 31:03.405
took care of him ourselves.

31:08.493 --> 31:10.704
And there was this friend of my dad,

31:11.580 --> 31:13.999
a guy he worked with for years, James.

31:16.502 --> 31:20.214
And he started...
really helping out.

31:21.590 --> 31:22.799
Helping my mom with stuff,

31:22.799 --> 31:25.093
like prepping the business
for when my dad was gone.

31:25.093 --> 31:26.970
My dad loved this guy.

31:29.139 --> 31:30.140
- Okay.

31:35.395 --> 31:37.564
- Uh, and then one time, I was alone

31:38.690 --> 31:39.983
with my dad.

31:41.193 --> 31:43.153
My mom had some appointment in the city.

31:43.153 --> 31:45.948
I don't remember what she said,
hair or some shit, I don't know.

31:47.032 --> 31:48.325
But I was alone with him.

31:51.954 --> 31:53.914
And he just started to crash.

32:02.589 --> 32:04.383
The thing that sucks is, like,

32:07.845 --> 32:10.389
I know a lot of people who are dying

32:10.389 --> 32:11.974
make peace with it.

32:15.936 --> 32:18.480
But my dad really didn't wanna die.

32:19.773 --> 32:20.941
He was, like...

32:23.443 --> 32:24.570
not ready.

32:31.326 --> 32:33.245
And when he started to crash, he knew.

32:35.497 --> 32:38.709
And I knew, and I started to panic.

32:38.709 --> 32:40.878
He kept asking for my mom,
and I kept calling her,

32:40.878 --> 32:42.379
and she wasn't answering.

32:48.010 --> 32:49.261
And then he just died.

32:52.806 --> 32:53.974
Alone, with me.

32:58.896 --> 33:01.190
And it wasn't till three hours later

33:01.190 --> 33:03.525
my mom actually got the calls.

33:05.777 --> 33:07.029
[sighs]

33:07.821 --> 33:08.822
MAX:
Fuck.

33:09.948 --> 33:10.991
I'm so sorry.

33:11.617 --> 33:12.618
That's awful.

33:15.996 --> 33:17.372
- Yeah, and there, there was no,

33:18.832 --> 33:20.000
there was no appointment.

33:25.005 --> 33:28.050
I found out later my mom
had been out fucking that guy James.

33:28.050 --> 33:30.802
Sleeping with him the entire time
my dad was dying.

33:31.303 --> 33:32.304
- Jesus.

33:38.769 --> 33:41.605
Does she know you know?
- No.

33:49.446 --> 33:52.032
I think she's... seeing him again.

33:52.032 --> 33:53.534
It's so fucking gross.

33:56.078 --> 33:57.079
- That's a lot.

33:57.829 --> 33:59.831
- I used to be a happier person.

34:05.128 --> 34:07.464
Wasn't so in my head all the time.

34:11.134 --> 34:13.262
Now I feel like the things
that do excite me,

34:13.262 --> 34:14.429
do get me out of my head,

34:14.429 --> 34:17.975
I don't even know if they're...
good for me.

34:24.356 --> 34:28.318
- Do you think maybe you're...
depressed?

34:29.987 --> 34:30.988
- Um--

34:34.658 --> 34:35.659
No?

34:39.580 --> 34:42.040
No, I think I'm sad.

34:42.040 --> 34:45.919
I think it's normal to be sad,
my dad died.

34:45.919 --> 34:48.630
- I'm not saying it's not normal,
I'm just saying it could explain a lot.

34:48.630 --> 34:50.299
- Explain what?
- Just stuff.

34:51.258 --> 34:52.259
I've noticed, like,

34:53.302 --> 34:54.720
how you go MIA a lot.

34:55.262 --> 34:56.638
- Okay.

34:56.638 --> 34:58.515
- Look, I'm just saying,

34:58.515 --> 35:00.434
I knew a lot of guys who had depression.

35:00.434 --> 35:02.853
- I just feel like putting a label on it

35:02.853 --> 35:04.146
kind of invalidates it.

35:04.146 --> 35:07.107
- It doesn't invalidate it.
That's an insane way to look at it.

35:08.483 --> 35:10.360
I'm not saying you're insane,

35:10.360 --> 35:13.780
I'm just saying, it's insane
to think about it that way.

35:13.780 --> 35:15.115
- I feel like I just
shouldn't have told you,

35:15.115 --> 35:17.409
because you're just judging me now.

35:17.409 --> 35:19.411
- No, I'm not.

35:20.704 --> 35:21.788
I'm glad you told me.

35:26.710 --> 35:28.587
- We don't know each other that well.

35:37.930 --> 35:38.931
- Really?

35:40.849 --> 35:41.850
- I mean, yeah.

35:41.850 --> 35:46.188
We haven't... been doing this
that long, so--

35:49.441 --> 35:50.901
- Doing what, exactly?

35:53.195 --> 35:56.073
You think I don't know
what's going on

35:56.073 --> 35:58.200
when I go weeks at a time
without hearing from you?

36:00.410 --> 36:01.411
I'm not an idiot.

36:06.291 --> 36:08.252
- Honestly, I think you should just

36:08.252 --> 36:10.045
be with someone nicer than me.

36:14.424 --> 36:15.884
- So, do you want me to leave?

36:31.900 --> 36:33.110
You're nice, Lucy.

36:36.530 --> 36:37.531
You're just

36:39.366 --> 36:41.368
really fucking immature.

36:44.454 --> 36:45.497
It's too much.

36:49.626 --> 36:52.546
[Diana and Stephen moaning]

37:04.141 --> 37:06.935
- Sorry you had to come

37:06.935 --> 37:08.228
all the way up here.

37:11.440 --> 37:12.733
- I know you hate it here.

37:16.361 --> 37:18.530
We're gonna get you something
in the city for the summer.

37:19.323 --> 37:20.490
I promise.

37:22.492 --> 37:24.286
- Why are you so good to me?

37:24.286 --> 37:25.287
- Hey.

37:27.706 --> 37:30.250
Partially because I like a challenge.

37:30.250 --> 37:31.668
- And the other part?

